steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"ceh9o","text":"Single-house mice in new cages containing activity wheels at least 3 days prior to beginning drug/vehicle to collect baseline data.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"4t5jk","text":"Place clear wheel base holder on cage floor. If the experiment involves providing medicated water, place water bottle in the cage with sufficient autoclaved water. Note that excessive bedding crowds the cage and can cause water leaks.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"b94m7","text":"Turn on the wheel base and ensure that it connects to the Hub. Connect the base to the orange wheel and test that it properly detects wheel spins by manually spinning the wheel and monitoring the spin count. If the wheel connects and counts properly, place the wheel in the cage.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"d23pt","text":"Label each cage with the wheel number, put mouse in cage, and place on rack. If providing medicated water, ensure the mouse does not have access to other water sources, such as a LixIt spout.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"artk5","text":"If cages cannot accommodate both wheels/water bottles and a food rack, provide food on the cage floor.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"7tkmr","text":"Monitor Hub connection daily, replacing activity wheel batteries as needed. Change cages every  two weeks.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"8bgjj","text":"At the end of each experiment, end data acquisition and clean all components with 10% bleach  and water.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"5tkfi","text":"Export wheel data file from Master Hub as an Excel sheet (Wheel Manager -\u003e Export Data).","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"9gju5","text":"To analyze data in Excel, take the average data from the light and dark cycles in the vivarium (e.g.  7pm-7am for each night, and 7am-7pm for each day).","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
